vi cheatsheet
1. select multiple lines
  shift + V
  after that moving the up/down key on the keyboard to select lines
2. move the selected lines to the left or right
  using < (shift + ,) to move selected lines to the left
  using > (shift + .) to move selected lines to the right

3. go to the specific line
  n + G to go to line n. e.g. "20 G" -> go to line 20

4. go to end of line
  $ will go to end of line
5. go to beginning of the line
  ^ will go to beginning of the line
